      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be documented with sources and nominal values; input uncertainty distributions must be characterized for UQ.",
      "rationale": "All 13 model inputs are documented with nominal values and uncertainty distributions derived from manufacturing tolerances and literature. Comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling across all inputs was performed to propagate input uncertainties through to the hemolysis index QoI, yielding a 95th-percentile RH of 0.87, well below the acceptance threshold of 1.0."
